The files in here can be copied (or linked) to the (CLM) directory containing
the top-level CMakeLists.txt file for unit tests. Then unit tests can be run on
my local machine (roo2) using:

make -j 4 -f Makefile.utest config
make -j 4 -f Makefile.utest test

For unit tests not run out of CLM, also need to specify CESM_ROOT_RELPATH, as
in:

make -j 4 -f Makefile.utest CESM_ROOT_RELPATH=../.. config
make -j 4 -f Makefile.utest CESM_ROOT_RELPATH=../.. test
